sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K872000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Signal converter, converts a HCO3- signal in a cAMP intermediate signal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is composed by the mild promoter J23101 with rbs B0012 attached to protein sAC and terminator B0030. Protein sAC (for soluble Adenilate Cyclase) is a 854 bp long and its function is to generate cAMP form ATP based on HCO3- concentration. This protein is involved in pH sensing, CO2 sensing and even in spermatozoa capacitance.
